      "description": "This 1995 Porsche 911 Carrera is a superlative, investment-grade example of the final air-cooled generation. The M64 3.6L flat-six remains matching-numbers and mechanically pristine, delivering linear power through a crisp G50 six-speed manual transaxle. The chassis is anchored by the sophisticated multi-link rear suspension and a factory-optioned limited-slip differential, ensuring peerless lateral grip and turn-in precision. Every component, from the four-piston Brembo-sourced calipers to the original Bilstein dampers, operates perfectly within factory tolerances. This is a rare opportunity to acquire a bone-dry, unmodified 993 in true showroom condition.",
